WEBVTT

00:04.671 --> 00:05.639 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.672 --> 00:06.640 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.673 --> 00:07.641 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And I'm Hari
Sreenivasan.

00:07.674 --> 00:09.610 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Gwen Ifill is away.

00:09.643 --> 00:12.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: A
powerful earthquake
hits Central Italy, toppling
towns and leaving

00:12.946 --> 00:17.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
more than 150 dead, as rescuers
scramble to
save those stuck under the
rubble.

00:17.751 --> 00:22.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also ahead this
Wednesday:
a look at the inner workings of
the Clinton

00:22.389 --> 00:27.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Foundation with its president,
and why it's
become so controversial for the
Democratic

00:27.127 --> 00:28.795 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Party's nominee.

00:28.829 --> 00:32.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And a popular
destination
for tourists, Iceland is
becoming home to

00:32.299 --> 00:36.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
refugees fleeing wars -- how the
close-knit
island is adapting to an influx
of outsiders.

00:36.970 --> 00:41.742 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KRISTIN ISLEIFSDOTTIR, Iceland:
I think of
our country as just a part of
the global village.

00:41.775 --> 00:45.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Nobody can decide where they're
born, and
I think everyone should have a
fair chance.

00:45.812 --> 00:53.387 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:53.420 --> 00:56.156 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:56.189 --> 01:06.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In today's early
morning hours,
Italy's countryside was jolted
awake by an

01:06.566 --> 01:11.571 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
earthquake, striking just
beneath the surface
and wreaking terrible havoc.

01:11.605 --> 01:18.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The official number of deaths
has reached
159, but that number is expected
to grow.

01:18.845 --> 01:24.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
An army of rescue workers
quickly descended
on three small Italian towns
that were leveled

01:24.952 --> 01:26.553 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the quake.

01:26.586 --> 01:30.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They were able to pull some
people from the
rubble, but others remain
trapped.

01:31.024 --> 01:36.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): I
heard people asking
for help, people calling out,
asking for help,

01:36.196 --> 01:37.831 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
but in this condition, what
could I do?

01:37.864 --> 01:40.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have been to the center, and
it's all in
rubble.

01:40.567 --> 01:46.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): We
came out to the
piazza, and it looked like
Dante's Inferno,

01:46.173 --> 01:48.542 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
people crying for help, help.

01:48.575 --> 01:53.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The 6.2-magnitude
earthquake
hit in the middle of the night,
just after

01:54.014 --> 01:55.782 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
3:30 a.m.

01:55.816 --> 02:02.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was felt across Central
Italy, but the
tiny towns of Amatrice,
Accumoli, and Pescara

02:02.522 --> 02:05.359 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
del Tronto were hardest-hit.

02:05.392 --> 02:11.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Italian Prime Minister Matteo
Renzi arrived
in Amatrice late today after
promising the

02:11.965 --> 02:13.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
area his full support.

02:13.900 --> 02:17.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MATTEO RENZI, Italian Prime
Minister (through
translator): This is a time when
we're allowed

02:17.904 --> 02:19.139 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to shed tears.

02:19.172 --> 02:21.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the faithful, it is a moment
to say a
prayer.

02:21.375 --> 02:24.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For everyone, it is a moment of
respect and
pain.

02:24.811 --> 02:31.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It's slow going
for the rescue
workers who are combing the
wreckage for survivors,

02:31.184 --> 02:33.153 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
oftentimes using only their
hands.

02:33.186 --> 02:39.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDREA GENTILI, Rescue Worker
(through translator):
We need chain saws, shears to
cut iron bars,

02:39.059 --> 02:40.794 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and jacks to remove beams.

02:40.827 --> 02:41.795 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Everything.

02:41.828 --> 02:43.730 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We need everything.

02:43.764 --> 02:49.169 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The hard work
paid off in Accumoli,
where a 65-year-old man was
pulled out of

02:49.202 --> 02:52.839 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the rubble after nine hours.

02:52.873 --> 02:57.811 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Applause followed the man as he
was loaded
into an ambulance.

02:57.844 --> 03:02.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We get an on-the-scene report
now from special
correspondent Christopher
Livesay, who is

03:02.716 --> 03:04.351 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in Amatrice, Italy.

03:04.384 --> 03:06.920 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We spoke just a short time ago.

03:06.953 --> 03:08.055 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Chris Livesay, welcome.

03:08.088 --> 03:11.358 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
First of all, you have been
there all day
long.

03:11.391 --> 03:13.126 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What are you seeing?

03:13.160 --> 03:15.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTOPHER LIVESAY: Well, I'm
seeing what
looks like the aftermath of a
war zone.

03:15.295 --> 03:19.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The imagery all around me is
much more similar
to what we're used to seeing
come out of places

03:19.599 --> 03:25.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
like Aleppo and Syria, not the
idyllic hillside
town of Amatrice.

03:25.138 --> 03:30.410 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Normally, this is a place where
tourists go
to escape the heat during the
summer, especially

03:30.444 --> 03:34.948 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the month of August, which in
Italy is the
national month of vacations.

03:34.981 --> 03:40.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So a town of normally 2,000
people had twice
the population this time of
year, only increasing

03:40.854 --> 03:43.156 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the amount of injuries and
fatalities, unfortunately.

03:43.190 --> 03:47.194 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: When people think
of Italy,
of course they think of history.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.362 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Just how widespread was the
damage?

03:49.396 --> 03:54.434 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTOPHER LIVESAY: The damage
stretches
all the way from the west coast
to the east

03:54.468 --> 03:56.203 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
coast.

03:56.236 --> 03:59.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, if you want a sense of
history and
culture, just look behind me at
the Church

03:59.172 --> 04:00.474 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of St. Augustine.

04:00.507 --> 04:03.210 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It dates back to the 14th
century.

04:03.243 --> 04:05.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Half of it is collapsed right
before your
eyes.

04:05.579 --> 04:08.181 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Only the belfry is really
standing.

04:08.215 --> 04:13.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's rather indicative of
the damage
that stretches all across
Central Italy, not

04:13.453 --> 04:18.758 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
just here in the region of Lazio
around Rome,
but also the nearby region of
Umbria, which

04:18.792 --> 04:22.762 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
has a number of artistic
heritage sites.

04:22.796 --> 04:28.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're talking not just in that
region, but
all across Central Italy,
buildings that range

04:28.435 --> 04:31.271 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from the Middle Ages to the
Renaissance.

04:31.304 --> 04:35.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's going to be all types of
loss, not
just of life, but, of course,
that is the

04:35.242 --> 04:38.411 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
most important thing that
everyone is rushing
to save.

04:38.445 --> 04:44.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People all around me, volunteers
and professionals
likewise, are working around the
clock to

04:44.317 --> 04:47.320 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
see if there are any survivors
still underneath
this rubble.

04:47.354 --> 04:51.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Do they have the
resources
they need, Chris, to get this
done?

04:51.224 --> 04:54.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTOPHER LIVESAY: They seem
to have all
the resources they need,
especially in terms

04:54.694 --> 04:56.596 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of manpower.

04:56.630 --> 05:03.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have been overwhelmed by the
amount of volunteers
and other rescue agencies from
firefighters

05:03.270 --> 05:08.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to ambulance drivers to civil
protection agents,
you name it.

05:08.108 --> 05:11.244 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Even the military is chipping in
at this point.

05:11.278 --> 05:14.648 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're all working around the
clock to help
people.

05:14.681 --> 05:16.650 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
You have tents.

05:16.683 --> 05:19.786 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You have cots that have been set
up in parks.

05:19.819 --> 05:24.658 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a sports center that has
been converted
into a makeshift dormitory.

05:24.691 --> 05:32.632 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, just in this town of
Amatrice, there are
temporary beds set up for
hundreds of people,

05:32.666 --> 05:35.802 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and that's the case all across
Italy right
now.

05:35.835 --> 05:38.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Thousands of temporary beds and
housing have
been set up.

05:38.305 --> 05:42.709 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So the people do appear to have
all the help
they need.

05:42.742 --> 05:48.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What they have working against
them is perhaps
the very thing that makes this
part of Italy

05:48.181 --> 05:53.220 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so picturesque, and that's the
fact that these
are small hilltop towns with
twisting and

05:53.253 --> 05:54.955 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
winding roads.

05:54.988 --> 06:01.461 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those roads were not made for
heavy vehicles,
lots of ambulances, one after
another.

06:01.494 --> 06:03.630 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're having to negotiate the
road.

06:03.663 --> 06:07.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Oftentimes, there's just not
enough space
for everyone to go in and out of
these place,

06:07.767 --> 06:12.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so they're relying heavily on
helicopters
to air evac people into nearby
hospital, but

06:12.939 --> 06:17.944 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
also hospitals as far afield as
Rome, which
is almost 100 miles from here.

06:17.978 --> 06:21.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Chris Livesay in
Amatrice,
thank you.

06:21.448 --> 06:25.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Five thousand
miles away
from Italy, another powerful
earthquake rocked

06:25.652 --> 06:27.654 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Myanmar today, killing at least
four people.

06:27.687 --> 06:32.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The 6.8-magnitude quake struck
near the town
of Chauk, 20 miles from the
former capital

06:32.859 --> 06:34.628 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Bagan.

06:34.661 --> 06:39.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Officials estimated almost 200
of Bagan's
centuries-old Buddhist pagodas
were damaged.

06:39.799 --> 06:43.536 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The devastation could have been
worse, had
the quake not hit so deep
underground.

06:43.570 --> 06:49.276 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Militants
attacked the American
University of Afghanistan in
Kabul, the capital,

06:49.309 --> 06:50.543 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
today.

06:50.577 --> 06:53.413 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At least one person was killed
and 18 more
were wounded.

06:53.446 --> 06:58.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Foreign staff and dozens of
students were
reportedly trapped inside the
compound.

06:58.918 --> 07:02.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Student witnesses said the
shooting lasted
for more than an hour.

07:02.289 --> 07:06.693 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ZIAUCOIN, Survivor (through
translator): First,
an explosion happened, and then
we heard the

07:06.726 --> 07:08.228 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
sound of gunfire.

07:08.261 --> 07:09.963 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Twenty of us were in the class.

07:09.996 --> 07:12.432 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Two bullets hit on the door of
our classroom.

07:12.465 --> 07:14.768 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All the boys escaped through the
window of
the class.

07:14.801 --> 07:17.871 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There was no
immediate claim
of responsibility.

07:17.904 --> 07:22.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is the second time this
month that the
university or its staff have
been targeted.

07:22.208 --> 07:27.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: In South
Sudan, at least
275 people have died in fighting
between government

07:27.113 --> 07:28.915 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
troops and rebel forces.

07:28.948 --> 07:33.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Each side blamed the other today
for launching
attacks in a northeastern town
less than a

07:33.386 --> 07:35.221 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
week ago.

07:35.255 --> 07:39.659 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those reports came after word
that opposition
leader Riek Machar, who'd
recently fled the

07:39.693 --> 07:42.395 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
country, is now in Sudan for
urgent medical
attention.

07:42.429 --> 07:48.468 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: North Korea's
successful launch
of a ballistic missile triggered
swift condemnation

07:48.501 --> 07:50.370 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
today.

07:50.403 --> 07:54.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was fired from a submarine,
and flew over
300 miles within range of
hitting South Korea

07:54.874 --> 07:56.443 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
