08:08.755 --> 08:13.860 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WANG YI, Chinese Foreign
Minister (through
translator): China opposes North
Korea's nuclear

08:13.893 --> 08:18.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
missile program, and opposes any
words or
deeds that could cause tensions
on the Korean

08:18.198 --> 08:19.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Peninsula.

08:19.966 --> 08:23.670 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
China will adhere to its
consistent and firm
stand of making persistent
efforts towards

08:23.703 --> 08:25.672 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
denuclearization on the
peninsula.

08:25.705 --> 08:30.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The U.S. State
Department echoed
that sentiment, saying its
commitment to protecting

08:30.210 --> 08:34.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
its allies in the region from
North Korean
aggression was -- quote --
"iron-clad."

08:34.214 --> 08:38.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And stocks
slipped on Wall
Street today, led by drops in
the health care

08:38.752 --> 08:40.353 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
