programs will remain
in the foundation.

32:50.535 --> 32:54.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The only thing I can assure you
at the moment
is the Clinton Library is going
to remain

32:54.673 --> 32:58.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the foundation and that the
president is
going to visit his foundation,
library.

32:58.410 --> 32:59.778 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: OK.

32:59.811 --> 33:05.750 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Thank you, Donna Shalala, the
president of
the Clinton Foundation.

33:05.784 --> 33:10.722 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thanks for joining us.

33:10.755 --> 33:14.192 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

33:14.226 --> 33:20.165 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": a
drastic spike
in the price of EpiPens used to
combat allergic

33:20.198 --> 33:24.836 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
reactions; and the astronomical
discovery
of an Earth-like planet.

33:24.870 --> 33:31.276 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first: Anti-immigrant
sentiment is on
the rise in Europe, and it has
spread to Iceland,

33:31.309 --> 33:36.281 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
one of the more unusual
destinations for refugees
from the war in Syria.

33:36.314 --> 33:41.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But many people on this island
nation in the
middle of the North Atlantic
welcome the prospect

33:41.586 --> 33:46.725 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of their traditionally white,
Christian country
becoming more multicultural.

33:46.758 --> 33:51.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Malcolm
Brabant reports
from the Icelandic capital,
Reykjavik.

33:51.563 --> 33:57.736 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Outside
Iceland's tiny Parliament,
pro-refugee supporters outnumber
and encircle

33:57.769 --> 34:03.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a group from a new party called
the Icelandic
National Front, which objects to
recent legislation

34:03.308 --> 34:05.510 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
relaxing rules on immigration.

34:05.543 --> 34:08.113 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One of their standard-bearers is
nurse Maria
Magnusdottir.

34:08.146 --> 34:12.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARIA MAGNUSDOTTIR, Icelandic
National Front:
We do not want people that are
not adapting

34:12.784 --> 34:16.087 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to our culture, like, for
example, Muslims.

34:16.121 --> 34:19.024 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm not saying that all Muslims
are bad people.

34:19.057 --> 34:24.162 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, unfortunately, they are not
adapting
to cultures.

34:24.195 --> 34:31.503 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, like, in Europe, we can see
two cultures
in most of those countries.

34:31.536 --> 34:34.539 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that is what we are afraid
of.

34:34.572 --> 34:38.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: One of the
cheerleaders on
the other side is Salmann
Tamimi, a Palestinian

34:38.510 --> 34:45.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
imam who stopped off in Iceland
en route to
North America in the 1970s, and
never left.

34:45.183 --> 34:51.589 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SALMANN TAMIMI, Imam: You see
how many supporters
are, five, six, 10 times more
than the other

34:51.623 --> 34:52.724 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
guys.

34:52.757 --> 34:55.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this is how the Icelandic
society is,
really.

34:55.360 --> 35:02.734 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have maybe 2 or 3 percent who
are what
I call racists and fascists.

35:02.767 --> 35:08.239 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And -- but the majority is nice
people and
we are happy for their support
that we are

35:08.273 --> 35:09.407 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
getting.

35:09.441 --> 35:18.283 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: The population is very
small here in
Iceland.

35:18.316 --> 35:19.651 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We are very few persons.

35:19.684 --> 35:25.056 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And if you open all the borders,
then we're
in trouble.

35:25.090 --> 35:30.195 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: "This is a
disgusting use
of the flag," shouts Logi
Stefansson, a well-known

35:30.228 --> 35:33.031 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
musician who shares Icelandic
and Angolan
heritage.

35:33.064 --> 35:35.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LOGI STEFANSSON, Musician: They
want to basically
keep the country white.

35:35.567 --> 35:41.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're talking about -- like,
they have 800
asylum-seekers coming next year,
which is,

35:41.039 --> 35:43.408 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
like, a disgraceful number.

35:43.441 --> 35:44.409 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's too small.

35:44.442 --> 35:45.910 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They just want the white
supremacy.

35:45.944 --> 35:51.549 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Like, seriously, the system for
asylum-seekers
in Iceland is disgusting.

35:51.583 --> 35:54.519 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They get treated like dogs.

35:54.552 --> 35:59.290 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But the
treatment afforded
the Al-Mohammad family from
Aleppo has been

35:59.324 --> 36:01.159 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
exemplary.

36:01.192 --> 36:05.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Al-Mohammads left Syria for
Lebanon in
2012, signed up for the U.N.
refugee resettlement

36:06.031 --> 36:09.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
program, and in January were
told that they
were going to Iceland.

36:09.100 --> 36:12.971 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Although it wasn't their choice,
English teacher
Khattab is not complaining.

36:13.004 --> 36:16.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KHATTAB AL-MOHAMMAD, Syrian
Refugee: This
is now the dream of most of the
Syrians, to

36:16.975 --> 36:24.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
restore the happiness of their
children and
find a means for making this
happen.

36:24.049 --> 36:31.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we were very lucky to be
here, for example,
and have this chance to play,
because other

36:31.790 --> 36:38.897 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
children in Syria now, they are
killed by
the -- our criminal president
and his supporters.

36:38.930 --> 36:45.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Al-Mohammad,
his wife, their
six children and his mother,
have been given

36:45.670 --> 36:50.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
an apartment in the middle-class
neighborhood
of Akureyri, a northern town
less than 40

36:50.642 --> 36:52.544 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
miles from the Arctic Circle.

36:52.577 --> 36:57.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KHATTAB AL-MOHAMMAD: We found a
lot of similarities
between the two societies, for
example, the

36:57.382 --> 37:02.854 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
