together.

38:44.155 --> 38:51.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a nation of just 330,000
people, it's much
easier to house refugees amongst
Icelanders.

38:51.496 --> 38:56.901 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The town's Red Cross has
organized a support
group whose purpose is to help
the newcomers

38:56.935 --> 38:58.670 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
find their feet and bloom.

38:58.703 --> 39:05.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KARI LAURSSON, Iceland: I hope
that, if at
some point, Iceland would go
sort of be a

39:05.510 --> 39:11.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
war zone or something like that,
someone somewhere
else on the planet would welcome
me as well

39:11.482 --> 39:13.351 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
as they possibly can.

39:13.384 --> 39:16.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KRISTIN ISLEIFSDOTTIR, Iceland:
I think of
our country as just a part of
the global village.

39:16.621 --> 39:20.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Nobody can decide where they're
born, and
I think everyone should have a
fair chance.

39:20.658 --> 39:24.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Two of the
volunteers are
heading out to the house of an
electrician

39:24.462 --> 39:28.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from Damascus called Joumaa
Naser, who lives
with his wife and their five
children.

39:28.700 --> 39:32.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NGIBJORG STEFANSDOTTIR, Red
Cross Volunteer:
They don't speak English but
they're very

39:32.270 --> 39:34.539 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
good at practicing Icelandic.

39:34.572 --> 39:37.041 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we are helping them to
learn.

39:37.075 --> 39:42.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I want to teach them how to be
themselves
in our society and to use the
Icelandic language.

39:42.580 --> 39:46.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: As the girls
help one of
the younger children with his
Icelandic, the

39:46.985 --> 39:51.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
town's cultural coordinator is
on hand to
translate a conversation between
one of the

39:51.723 --> 39:56.160 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sons, who is just about to start
high school,
and his new teachers.

39:56.194 --> 40:00.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Joumaa Naser's skills as an
electrician are
in demand, and he's happy to be
working.

40:00.331 --> 40:04.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOUMAA NASER, Syrian Refugee
(through translator):
In the long term future, we
haven't yet decided

40:04.736 --> 40:06.104 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
