52:55.939 --> 52:58.075 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so ultimately you can
develop some real
speed.

52:58.108 --> 53:03.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, potentially, some ideas on
the drawing
board could make that trip of
four light years

53:03.113 --> 53:06.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
something on the order of a
century or maybe
a little less.

53:06.083 --> 53:10.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Right now, if you wanted to,
say, launch the
space shuttle, not that it could
go there,

53:10.587 --> 53:15.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
